HEADWORD: Macrometer
<hw>Ma*crom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Macro-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
for determining the size or distance of inaccessible objects by means of
two reflectors on a common sextant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

